rComments: Pros: Passionate about subject, well informed / aware Fluid teaching style / considerate of students  Cons: Sometimes rambles Extremely long powerpoints sometimes drag lecture on

Paul York's class was non-traditional, but completely changed my outlook on the world. His lectures can be a bit rambling, but he is passionate about what he studies. And a bonus if you like dogs - he often brought his rescue dogs to class! :)
very friendly + knowledgeable + understanding in terms of assignments ... learned a lot in his class!
